The paper discusses the use of simulated environments for conducting experiments in complex robotic systems, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions topics such as optimisation of bipedal locomotion and planning complex multi-agent strategies, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The use of simulations for replicable and statistically-robust research is also relevant to systems and control (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG).
